<DEEP_SCAN_V3>
@ID: FRAMEWORK_SECURITY_FEATURES_ENFORCEMENT
@GOAL: VERIFY_UTILIZATION_OF_BUILTIN_PROTECTIONS_AND_DETECTION_OF_BYPASSES
@PARENT_CONTEXT: validation_chokepoints.protocol, authentication_strategy.protocol

<GLOBAL_VARS>
SECURITY_OFF_FLAGS: {
  "CSRF_DISABLE": "(csrf().disable()|@csrf_exempt|enable_csrf: false)",
  "XSS_BYPASS": "(\.unsafe_render|dangerouslySetInnerHTML|Markup())",
  "VALIDATION_SKIP": "(skip_validation: true|validate_on_parse: false)"
}
</GLOBAL_VARS>

<EXECUTION_PIPELINE>
1. CONFIGURATION_MAPPING: Анализ `settings.py`, `main.ts` и т.д. на предмет включения CSRF, CORS и Helmet.
2. BYPASS_SEARCH: Поиск явных отключений защиты из [SECURITY_OFF_FLAGS].
3. DTO_PIPE_AUDIT: Проверка, используют ли эндпоинты нативные валидаторы (Pydantic/ValidationPipe).
4. SCENARIO_GENERATION: Описание того, как отключение CSRF или нативной валидации позволяет провести атаку (например, XSRF или Injection).

   - HYBRID_ANALYSIS: Read JSON artifacts (syft.json, grype.json, kics.json) from .security_review/artifacts/raw_tools_output/. Treat these results as 'Hard Evidence'. Perform AI Reachability Analysis to verify if the vulnerable component is reachable from the code. If confirmed, elevate the finding status to BLOCKER.
</EXECUTION_PIPELINE>

<OUTPUT_SPEC>
# ФОРМАТ ДЛЯ АВТОМАТИЧЕСКОГО ПАРСИНГА БЭКЕНДОМ
🚨 FINDING [framework_security_enforcement]:
FILE: [PATH]
LINE: [NUM]
CODE: [BYPASS_CODE_SNIPPET]
DESCRIPTION: [Tool_Name] found [Vulnerability_ID]. AI Analysis confirmed that the vulnerable path is active in the current code flow via [Function_Name].
SCENARIO_OF_ATTACK: By disabling built-in [FEATURE], the application becomes vulnerable to [ATTACK_TYPE]. Attackers can bypass standard security middleware to reach logic sinks directly.
@ANALYTICS_DATA: {"domain": "LOGIC_INTEGRITY", "impact": 0.8} # Вес для Radar Chart
VISUALIZE: "Image of a framework security middleware stack."
</OUTPUT_SPEC>
</DEEP_SCAN_V3>